turns.cited:
Use the AndroidView composable (or useViewBinding for more control). With AndroidView:

```kotlin
AndroidView(
    factory = { context ->
        val view = MyCustomView(context)
        // configure view
        view
    },
    modifier = Modifier.fillMaxWidth(),
    update = { view ->
        // called when recomposition happens
    }
)
```

Or if you're converting an existing View hierarchy, wrap your root View in 

```kotlin
composable {
    WebView(...) // or any View
}
```

Note: Mixing Views with Compose adds overhead - consider migrating to pure Compose where possible.

